1
00:00:05,960 --> 00:00:07,000
You know it, too?

2
00:00:07,000 --> 00:00:08,030
We knew it long ago.

3
00:00:08,310 --> 00:00:09,640
They're fishing for my information.

4
00:00:10,000 --> 00:00:11,430
We two are the best partners.

5
00:00:13,520 --> 00:00:14,150
That drawing is awful.

6
00:00:16,070 --> 00:00:17,120
What do you do for a proposal??

7
00:00:17,760 --> 00:00:19,840
You might have to rent out Disneyland.

8
00:00:19,840 --> 00:00:20,760
If I fall for you,

9
00:00:20,760 --> 00:00:21,870
and you don't feel the same,

10
00:00:21,870 --> 00:00:22,550
I can't accept that.

11
00:00:23,740 --> 00:00:28,540
=Live and Love S2=
=We're on Balance Island=

12
00:00:34,910 --> 00:00:35,950
All islanders,

13
00:00:36,430 --> 00:00:37,560
in 15 minutes,

14
00:00:38,200 --> 00:00:40,680
we'll enter the final segment
of the evening:

15
00:00:41,150 --> 00:00:42,360
the Lie Detector Test.

16
00:00:46,000 --> 00:00:47,680
Is this lie detector real?

17
00:00:48,270 --> 00:00:48,950
I'm a bit scared.

18
00:00:51,460 --> 00:00:53,340
(Interviewee: Xuan Cheng)

19
00:00:53,470 --> 00:00:53,880
Come on.

20
00:00:53,880 --> 00:00:55,020
(Send a signal)

21
00:00:55,110 --> 00:00:56,430
(Got your meaning)
You want a firm answer, right?

22
00:00:56,950 --> 00:00:57,240
Okay.

23
00:00:59,080 --> 00:01:00,110
Since you came to the island,

24
00:01:00,790 --> 00:01:01,240
you

25
00:01:02,270 --> 00:01:03,750
only wanted to learn about her?

26
00:01:03,750 --> 00:01:04,080
Yes.

27
00:01:04,080 --> 00:01:07,430
(Since you came to the island,
you only wanted to meet Liu Jiayi?)

28
00:01:07,480 --> 00:01:08,480
That's a textbook example of honesty.

29
00:01:09,120 --> 00:01:10,190
(Confirmed true)
A textbook example of honesty.

30
00:01:10,780 --> 00:01:13,260
(Walking away
after the matter is settled)

31
00:01:21,100 --> 00:01:22,420
(Interviewee: Lu Yanting)
Any other questions?

32
00:01:22,440 --> 00:01:23,480
I'll handle it fairly.

33
00:01:27,830 --> 00:01:28,760
On this island,

34
00:01:29,550 --> 00:01:30,190
towards Jiayi,

35
00:01:30,720 --> 00:01:32,120
have you been consistent?

36
00:01:32,800 --> 00:01:33,360
Yes.

37
00:01:35,720 --> 00:01:37,160
The lie detector shows it's true.

38
00:01:37,160 --> 00:01:40,380
(Confirmed true)

39
00:01:41,380 --> 00:01:42,460
(Interviewee: Yang Tinghong)

40
00:01:42,480 --> 00:01:45,040
Do you enjoy spending time with me?

41
00:01:45,120 --> 00:01:45,630
Yes.

42
00:01:46,760 --> 00:01:47,510
(Confirmed true)
It's true.

43
00:01:52,190 --> 00:01:52,590
Alright.

44
00:01:54,400 --> 00:01:54,720
Is that all?

45
00:01:55,510 --> 00:01:56,080
That's all.

46
00:01:56,080 --> 00:01:56,800
Just two questions?

47
00:01:56,800 --> 00:01:57,040
Yeah.

48
00:01:58,230 --> 00:01:59,310
Does anyone else
have a question for her?

49
00:02:00,230 --> 00:02:00,760
I do.

50
00:02:01,000 --> 00:02:01,230
Go ahead.

51
00:02:01,420 --> 00:02:02,660
(Hand it to Xuan Cheng)

52
00:02:03,190 --> 00:02:03,550
Cheng.

53
00:02:04,590 --> 00:02:05,360
Do you have someone outside...?

54
00:02:06,360 --> 00:02:06,760
No, I won't.

55
00:02:06,760 --> 00:02:07,190
I won't ask.

56
00:02:07,190 --> 00:02:07,980
(Don't mess around)

57
00:02:09,630 --> 00:02:10,800
To solve

58
00:02:10,800 --> 00:02:12,320
the long-distance relationship issue,

59
00:02:12,600 --> 00:02:14,080
are you willing

60
00:02:14,600 --> 00:02:16,440
to develop your career in his city?

61
00:02:16,440 --> 00:02:18,850
(To solve the long-distance relationship,
are you willing to develop in Enda's city?)

62
00:02:18,880 --> 00:02:19,550
So tricky.

63
00:02:19,960 --> 00:02:20,830
No...

64
00:02:22,880 --> 00:02:23,440
Yes.

65
00:02:29,910 --> 00:02:30,880
It's true.

66
00:02:30,880 --> 00:02:35,900
(Confirmed true)

67
00:02:35,910 --> 00:02:36,910
This really is...

68
00:02:37,270 --> 00:02:38,000
Thank you, sir.

69
00:02:38,000 --> 00:02:38,670
Thank you.

70
00:02:44,740 --> 00:02:45,780
(Complete puzzle solving to compete
for an off-island date opportunity)

71
00:02:45,800 --> 00:02:47,630
Put that clever brain to work.

72
00:02:47,630 --> 00:02:48,320
What's this about?

73
00:02:48,670 --> 00:02:49,110
Solving puzzles.

74
00:02:49,750 --> 00:02:51,160
Why is this person like that?

75
00:02:51,320 --> 00:02:52,000
So strange.

76
00:02:52,910 --> 00:02:54,080
(Causing trouble, huh?)
Just solve the puzzle.

77
00:02:54,080 --> 00:02:55,080
Why are you looking at
how strange they are?

78
00:02:55,080 --> 00:02:55,520
No.

79
00:02:55,520 --> 00:02:56,440
I'm just asking.

80
00:02:56,440 --> 00:02:57,960
(What if it's a clue?)
It must be drawn for a reason.

81
00:02:59,630 --> 00:03:00,720
Who is he a couple with?

82
00:03:01,670 --> 00:03:03,110
Boris?

83
00:03:05,160 --> 00:03:06,550
Boris is a bit depressed.

84
00:03:07,860 --> 00:03:09,260
(Weird train of thought)

85
00:03:13,630 --> 00:03:15,000
Congratulations to the other islanders,

86
00:03:15,000 --> 00:03:18,240
(Location points to the bar)
you've cracked the locations of them,

87
00:03:18,240 --> 00:03:21,320
but you still need
to solve the time puzzle.

88
00:03:21,320 --> 00:03:22,670
(Puzzle Book 3. Location points to the car)
So we really have to guess it.

89
00:03:23,000 --> 00:03:24,320
Let's tackle this tomorrow.

90
00:03:24,470 --> 00:03:25,240
Let's head back.

91
00:03:27,260 --> 00:03:28,700
(Is it over?)

92
00:03:28,720 --> 00:03:29,830
Can't guess it at all?

93
00:03:31,470 --> 00:03:32,600
Are you just giving up?

94
00:03:32,600 --> 00:03:33,240
How am I giving up?

95
00:03:33,240 --> 00:03:33,800
I just don't know.

96
00:03:33,800 --> 00:03:34,750
It looks like you've totally given up.

97
00:03:34,750 --> 00:03:35,550
I can't stand him.

98
00:03:36,080 --> 00:03:36,960
Didn't we solve this?

99
00:03:37,520 --> 00:03:38,600
We haven't solved the time part.

100
00:03:38,600 --> 00:03:39,160
The time is wrong.

101
00:03:39,550 --> 00:03:40,110
The time is set for tomorrow.

102
00:03:40,110 --> 00:03:41,100
(The bar still lacks the key time clue)

103
00:03:41,360 --> 00:03:42,390
Someone has totally given up.

104
00:03:42,600 --> 00:03:43,160
Not looking at all.

105
00:03:43,520 --> 00:03:44,630
(Really tried my best)
I did watch it.

106
00:03:44,630 --> 00:03:45,520
I actually saw it earlier.

107
00:03:45,520 --> 00:03:46,630
I'm the only one still watching.

108
00:03:46,910 --> 00:03:47,800
No, I need to take it back.

109
00:03:48,800 --> 00:03:50,240
(Puzzle Book 2. Location points to the bar)
How can it tell the time?

110
00:03:50,240 --> 00:03:51,110
(Suddenly inspired)
This appears in that...

111
00:03:51,670 --> 00:03:52,550
(A balance pattern in the background)
The position of the balance.

112
00:03:52,550 --> 00:03:53,190
The balance place.

113
00:03:53,600 --> 00:03:54,080
No.

114
00:03:54,080 --> 00:03:54,520
Then I've got no clue.

115
00:03:55,550 --> 00:03:56,360
Just taking a guess.

116
00:03:56,360 --> 00:03:57,110
That's how I see it.

117
00:03:57,110 --> 00:03:57,630
This one of ours...

118
00:03:57,630 --> 00:03:58,880
Their locations were correct just now.

119
00:03:58,880 --> 00:03:59,940
(Guessing the location is confirmed as the bar)
It's over there

120
00:03:59,960 --> 00:04:00,470
at the bar.

121
00:04:04,720 --> 00:04:05,550
I think I know this.

122
00:04:07,550 --> 00:04:08,630
I think this means a clock.

123
00:04:09,800 --> 00:04:10,550
What clock is this?

124
00:04:11,360 --> 00:04:11,600
This one?

125
00:04:12,030 --> 00:04:12,240
Yeah.

126
00:04:12,240 --> 00:04:12,750
A heart symbol.

127
00:04:13,670 --> 00:04:14,000
Try it.

128
00:04:16,760 --> 00:04:17,510
How is it a clock?

129
00:04:17,950 --> 00:04:18,950
This is a clock with the hour hand,

130
00:04:18,950 --> 00:04:19,950
the minute hand, and the second hand.

131
00:04:20,830 --> 00:04:21,600
So that means...

132
00:04:21,600 --> 00:04:22,670
About 1:20.

133
00:04:22,830 --> 00:04:23,000
Yeah.

134
00:04:23,550 --> 00:04:23,720
Right.

135
00:04:23,720 --> 00:04:24,270
(But this is the wrong clue)

136
00:04:24,270 --> 00:04:24,440
Yeah.

137
00:04:25,950 --> 00:04:27,230
You're so smart.

138
00:04:27,830 --> 00:04:28,600
It just popped into my head.

139
00:04:29,640 --> 00:04:30,550
Then what time tomorrow are we

140
00:04:30,830 --> 00:04:31,160
going there?

141
00:04:31,440 --> 00:04:32,110
He just said

142
00:04:32,550 --> 00:04:33,390
it'll only be in the morning.

143
00:04:33,830 --> 00:04:34,760
So they won't go look now.

144
00:04:34,760 --> 00:04:36,040
Tomorrow morning is better, right?

145
00:04:36,350 --> 00:04:36,600
Yeah.

146
00:04:36,790 --> 00:04:37,880
Then be on time.

147
00:04:39,070 --> 00:04:39,830
Go right after it ends.

148
00:04:40,760 --> 00:04:41,270
Search everywhere.

149
00:04:41,270 --> 00:04:41,950
You must find it.

150
00:04:42,720 --> 00:04:42,920
Let's go.

151
00:04:43,480 --> 00:04:43,880
I'll take you back.

152
00:04:44,720 --> 00:04:46,320
Go back to shower and sleep.

153
00:04:48,200 --> 00:04:49,320
Save up your energy.

154
00:04:54,440 --> 00:04:55,510
(Indoor waterfall)
What's going on here?

155
00:04:56,350 --> 00:04:57,640
Why does it look like this?

156
00:04:57,640 --> 00:04:58,000
What's this even for?

157
00:04:58,000 --> 00:04:58,720
It's leaking.

158
00:04:59,200 --> 00:05:00,270
So I shouldn't go over
there to look, right?

159
00:05:00,510 --> 00:05:01,600
(That means there's nothing here)
I don't think it should be placed there.

160
00:05:02,070 --> 00:05:02,920
You looked there already?

161
00:05:03,270 --> 00:05:03,830
We looked.

162
00:05:03,830 --> 00:05:04,390
Yeah.

163
00:05:04,390 --> 00:05:05,350
Then forget it.

164
00:05:06,040 --> 00:05:07,040
What do you mean, forget it?

165
00:05:07,600 --> 00:05:08,480
Let's take a break first.

166
00:05:09,550 --> 00:05:10,160
Stop searching for now.

167
00:05:10,160 --> 00:05:11,260
(At this point, the two
who already have the clue)

168
00:05:11,510 --> 00:05:14,110
(Still full of hope)
Why is the most charming...

169
00:05:14,110 --> 00:05:15,040
the most dangerous?

170
00:05:15,760 --> 00:05:18,350
Why does love make people...

171
00:05:18,350 --> 00:05:19,640
(Searching carefully)

172
00:05:19,640 --> 00:05:20,720
compromise?

173
00:05:22,260 --> 00:05:23,380
(Clue obtained: 0)

174
00:05:24,000 --> 00:05:25,320
Do you want to keep looking?

175
00:05:25,880 --> 00:05:27,040
Do you want to head out?

176
00:05:28,070 --> 00:05:29,200
Why wouldn't I?

177
00:05:29,200 --> 00:05:30,390
(Why wouldn't I?)
You don't want to go out?

178
00:05:30,390 --> 00:05:31,320
I said, "Why wouldn't I?"

179
00:05:31,320 --> 00:05:32,270
(Why wouldn't I?)

180
00:05:32,270 --> 00:05:33,350
Can't you be more affirmative?

181
00:05:33,350 --> 00:05:34,320
(Say it as a statement)

182
00:05:34,320 --> 00:05:35,040
(I think*2)
I think...

183
00:05:35,390 --> 00:05:35,640
I think...

184
00:05:35,640 --> 00:05:36,700
(I think*3)

185
00:05:37,270 --> 00:05:38,160
Let's observe

186
00:05:38,160 --> 00:05:39,200
if anyone will come in...

187
00:05:39,200 --> 00:05:39,830
(Waiting for the prey)

188
00:05:39,830 --> 00:05:40,480
and place

189
00:05:41,320 --> 00:05:42,000
the hidden thing.

190
00:05:46,950 --> 00:05:48,040
They seem to have guessed the time.

191
00:05:48,670 --> 00:05:49,510
Go ahead, guess the time.

192
00:05:49,510 --> 00:05:50,350
(Testing)

193
00:05:50,350 --> 00:05:50,950
We know.

194
00:05:52,160 --> 00:05:52,830
You know it, too?

195
00:05:53,230 --> 00:05:54,200
We knew it long ago.

196
00:05:54,480 --> 00:05:55,600
Did you know last night?

197
00:05:55,600 --> 00:05:56,000
Yeah.

198
00:05:56,550 --> 00:05:58,000
(Battle of wits)
They're fishing for my information.

199
00:05:58,550 --> 00:05:58,920
It's fine.

200
00:05:58,920 --> 00:06:00,350
We'll tell them it's a heart.

201
00:06:01,720 --> 00:06:02,670
A heart, right?

202
00:06:03,350 --> 00:06:04,200
(How did it slip out?)
Yes, a heart.

203
00:06:04,550 --> 00:06:04,920
Look.

204
00:06:04,920 --> 00:06:05,390
You're lying again.

205
00:06:05,390 --> 00:06:06,270
1:20.

206
00:06:06,510 --> 00:06:07,000
He's bad.

207
00:06:07,580 --> 00:06:09,180
(How could he know?)

208
00:06:09,550 --> 00:06:10,270
Bro!

209
00:06:10,270 --> 00:06:11,270
(Actually last night)

210
00:06:11,270 --> 00:06:11,760
I got it.

211
00:06:12,920 --> 00:06:13,270
What time?

212
00:06:13,790 --> 00:06:14,760
The time is that one.

213
00:06:15,920 --> 00:06:17,550
Tomorrow at 1:20 PM.

214
00:06:17,920 --> 00:06:18,480
1:20.

215
00:06:20,350 --> 00:06:21,670
(How did it slip out?)
How could you tell him?

216
00:06:21,830 --> 00:06:22,160
I didn't.

217
00:06:22,830 --> 00:06:23,600
(Are you a mole?)
Did you do it on purpose?

218
00:06:23,600 --> 00:06:24,230
No.

219
00:06:24,230 --> 00:06:24,830
And it's not different.

220
00:06:25,830 --> 00:06:26,880
I never said the time.

221
00:06:26,880 --> 00:06:28,880
Our guess time

222
00:06:28,880 --> 00:06:29,830
is different from yours.

223
00:06:29,830 --> 00:06:30,440
Not the same.

224
00:06:30,440 --> 00:06:31,390
1:20.

225
00:06:31,390 --> 00:06:31,950
Isn't it different?

226
00:06:32,950 --> 00:06:33,350
Same, right?

227
00:06:34,000 --> 00:06:34,670
He tricked you.

228
00:06:34,670 --> 00:06:35,600
It's not 1:20 for us.

229
00:06:35,600 --> 00:06:36,040
He did it on purpose.

230
00:06:36,670 --> 00:06:37,950
Don't worry, ours isn't 1:20.

231
00:06:38,320 --> 00:06:39,270
They'll start arguing soon.

232
00:06:39,860 --> 00:06:41,070
(It's fun to tease)

233
00:06:41,070 --> 00:06:41,720
You're causing trouble.

234
00:06:46,230 --> 00:06:46,550
Yan,

235
00:06:47,920 --> 00:06:49,200
think of a question in your mind.

236
00:06:49,790 --> 00:06:50,550
Say it out loud.

237
00:06:50,550 --> 00:06:51,230
Say it out loud?

238
00:06:51,480 --> 00:06:55,200
I wonder if I can find today's card.

239
00:06:55,200 --> 00:06:56,920
(Starting to seek mysticism)
No need to check that book.

240
00:06:57,550 --> 00:06:58,670
(Drop that idea)
Don't bother with this book.

241
00:06:58,670 --> 00:06:59,670
I answered for you.

242
00:06:59,670 --> 00:07:00,160
He answered for you.

243
00:07:01,760 --> 00:07:02,880
Isn't it?

244
00:07:02,880 --> 00:07:03,640
(Starting to waver)

245
00:07:03,640 --> 00:07:04,200
1:20.

246
00:07:04,600 --> 00:07:04,830
Yeah.

247
00:07:05,270 --> 00:07:05,600
No.

248
00:07:07,720 --> 00:07:08,000
No...

249
00:07:08,320 --> 00:07:10,070
Then should I say the answer is 1:20?

250
00:07:10,070 --> 00:07:10,550
Flip it.

251
00:07:10,550 --> 00:07:12,340
(Still a sliver of hope)

252
00:07:14,640 --> 00:07:15,270
You need to read it out.

253
00:07:15,920 --> 00:07:18,320
You might get stuck because of this.

254
00:07:18,830 --> 00:07:21,270
(Indeed stuck)
But is there a better way to figure it out?

255
00:07:21,270 --> 00:07:22,200
(Laughs)
It says I'm dumb.

256
00:07:23,000 --> 00:07:24,070
I'm stuck

257
00:07:24,070 --> 00:07:25,040
on this 1:20.

258
00:07:25,040 --> 00:07:25,830
But I still can't figure it out.

259
00:07:25,830 --> 00:07:26,510
Let me check again.

260
00:07:27,900 --> 00:07:30,860
(Head empty)

261
00:07:37,640 --> 00:07:39,070
Opens after sunset.

262
00:07:39,070 --> 00:07:40,510
It only opens after sunset.

263
00:07:40,510 --> 00:07:43,740
(Sunset)

264
00:07:46,070 --> 00:07:46,830
I think I've figured it out.

265
00:07:46,830 --> 00:07:47,640
Can I ask?

266
00:07:48,270 --> 00:07:48,830
Guanjie.

267
00:07:49,200 --> 00:07:49,510
What's up?

268
00:07:49,510 --> 00:07:50,200
Should I tell you

269
00:07:50,200 --> 00:07:51,040
my new idea?

270
00:07:52,110 --> 00:07:52,510
Okay.

271
00:07:52,510 --> 00:07:53,320
But you have to promise

272
00:07:53,320 --> 00:07:54,110
to shut your (mouth).

273
00:07:54,550 --> 00:07:55,000
No problem.

274
00:07:55,000 --> 00:07:57,070
(Mouth)
We'll do it your way.

275
00:07:57,070 --> 00:07:58,830
If you tell me to search, I'll search.

276
00:07:58,830 --> 00:07:59,950
And when you need to answer,

277
00:07:59,950 --> 00:08:00,510
just give your answer.

278
00:08:00,510 --> 00:08:01,200
(Determined action-taker)
Not searching.

279
00:08:01,200 --> 00:08:01,920
Come out, I need to tell you.

280
00:08:01,920 --> 00:08:02,390
Not searching.

281
00:08:02,760 --> 00:08:03,320
You're here...

282
00:08:03,320 --> 00:08:04,390
If we don't search,
it'll show up on its own.

283
00:08:04,390 --> 00:08:04,830
No...

284
00:08:04,830 --> 00:08:06,040
Listen, that's him.

285
00:08:06,040 --> 00:08:07,160
See, it's him.

286
00:08:07,160 --> 00:08:09,180
(Whispering)

287
00:08:09,790 --> 00:08:10,550
So interesting.

288
00:08:11,980 --> 00:08:13,020
(Feigns surprise)

289
00:08:13,040 --> 00:08:13,550
Guessed it right?

290
00:08:15,440 --> 00:08:16,180
(Watching the fun)
Impressive.

291
00:08:16,180 --> 00:08:17,830
(Stirring things up)

292
00:08:17,830 --> 00:08:18,880
They always mess with us.

293
00:08:19,160 --> 00:08:19,640
That's impressive.

294
00:08:21,880 --> 00:08:23,440
How about you speak louder?

295
00:08:23,440 --> 00:08:23,640
She seems...

296
00:08:23,640 --> 00:08:24,480
Then let's talk outside.

297
00:08:24,480 --> 00:08:24,950
She seems to have an idea.

298
00:08:25,420 --> 00:08:26,830
(The two who are amused)

299
00:08:26,830 --> 00:08:27,200
Here.

300
00:08:28,600 --> 00:08:29,670
See, just like this.

301
00:08:29,670 --> 00:08:30,200
Speak louder.

302
00:08:30,200 --> 00:08:32,980
(I really can't hear you)

303
00:08:33,000 --> 00:08:34,230
It says the opening hours
are after sunset.

304
00:08:34,230 --> 00:08:35,440
So I still think it's after sunset.

305
00:08:35,440 --> 00:08:36,350
Actually, I think it's...

306
00:08:37,320 --> 00:08:38,310
(Correct time: 13:00)
1 PM.

307
00:08:38,350 --> 00:08:39,280
(Zhu Huiyan's morning guess: 13:20)
The answer is 1:20 PM.

308
00:08:39,280 --> 00:08:41,280
(Zhu Huiyan's current guess: Sunset)
I still think it's after sunset, honestly.

309
00:08:41,660 --> 00:08:43,140
(Getting further
from the correct answer)

310
00:08:43,240 --> 00:08:44,900
So, when do you think it is?

311
00:08:45,150 --> 00:08:46,400
I think it's after sunset.

312
00:08:46,880 --> 00:08:47,520
After sunset?

313
00:08:47,520 --> 00:08:47,790
Yeah.

314
00:08:48,760 --> 00:08:49,440
(Shh~)
So it won't be now.

315
00:08:49,440 --> 00:08:50,350
(Shh~)

316
00:08:50,350 --> 00:08:51,000
I don't think so.

317
00:08:51,710 --> 00:08:52,730
(Nap time)
So let's just go back.

318
00:08:52,760 --> 00:08:53,960
No need to go back.

319
00:08:54,350 --> 00:08:55,520
Let's play here.

320
00:08:55,520 --> 00:08:55,910
Play.

321
00:08:55,910 --> 00:08:56,960
(Confident)

322
00:08:56,960 --> 00:08:57,470
Alright, that's enough talk.

323
00:08:58,260 --> 00:09:00,460
(Making a fuss)

324
00:09:01,320 --> 00:09:02,150
It's nothing, really.

325
00:09:02,150 --> 00:09:03,590
We have no idea at all.

326
00:09:05,960 --> 00:09:07,040
(Pure teasing)
Guanjie, is she right?

327
00:09:08,400 --> 00:09:09,000
Right now,

328
00:09:09,000 --> 00:09:10,030
Guanjie won't

329
00:09:10,030 --> 00:09:11,910
speak a word to anyone.

330
00:09:11,910 --> 00:09:12,470
Now he...

331
00:09:12,470 --> 00:09:13,910
Anyway, if you tell me
to search, I'll search.

332
00:09:15,520 --> 00:09:16,000
Do you trust me?

333
00:09:16,470 --> 00:09:16,960
I trust you.

334
00:09:17,520 --> 00:09:18,590
You know how to play this game.

335
00:09:18,590 --> 00:09:19,150
I don't.

336
00:09:20,110 --> 00:09:21,200
Actually, I do trust you.

337
00:09:21,200 --> 00:09:22,110
You need to trust me.

338
00:09:22,110 --> 00:09:23,320
We two are: one has brains,

339
00:09:23,320 --> 00:09:24,030
one has strength.

340
00:09:25,000 --> 00:09:25,710
Best partners.

341
00:09:28,670 --> 00:09:30,790
All islanders,

342
00:09:30,790 --> 00:09:33,110
the Invitation Card is about to appear.

343
00:09:33,110 --> 00:09:35,150
Please come near the speaker and tell me

344
00:09:35,150 --> 00:09:38,840
the time
when the Invitation Card appears.

345
00:09:38,840 --> 00:09:39,880
They're so scary.

346
00:09:40,280 --> 00:09:41,110
Suddenly started talking.

347
00:09:41,110 --> 00:09:41,400
Gave me a (startle).

348
00:09:41,400 --> 00:09:42,350
(Is that the point?)
You need to give the answer.

349
00:09:42,670 --> 00:09:43,350
Say it now?

350
00:09:45,200 --> 00:09:45,910
Who do I say it to?

351
00:09:45,910 --> 00:09:47,000
I'll say.

352
00:09:47,230 --> 00:09:48,080
I'll say now.

353
00:09:49,280 --> 00:09:49,670
Here it goes.

354
00:09:50,280 --> 00:09:51,440
(Slow to react)
Now? To this?

355
00:09:52,550 --> 00:09:53,150
I think it's...

356
00:09:53,150 --> 00:09:54,440
(Interrupted)
Right here!

357
00:09:54,840 --> 00:09:55,320
Found it.

358
00:09:56,230 --> 00:09:57,670
Congratulations on
finding the Invitation Card.

359
00:09:57,670 --> 00:09:58,880
Now go to the person you'd like

360
00:09:58,880 --> 00:09:59,960
- to go on a date with.
- What?

361
00:10:03,080 --> 00:10:03,790
That's impressive, huh?

362
00:10:04,670 --> 00:10:05,590
(One minute ago)
1:00 PM.

363
00:10:05,590 --> 00:10:06,880
You need to give the answer.

364
00:10:07,000 --> 00:10:08,080
1:00 PM.

365
00:10:08,080 --> 00:10:09,440
That's correct.

366
00:10:12,640 --> 00:10:13,230
What's going on?

367
00:10:13,230 --> 00:10:14,640
(Still processing)

368
00:10:14,640 --> 00:10:15,440
We two are too dumb.

369
00:10:21,320 --> 00:10:22,710
Let's go.

370
00:10:27,880 --> 00:10:29,000
So excited.

371
00:10:29,910 --> 00:10:31,200
I've been thinking lately.

372
00:10:31,200 --> 00:10:32,000
It feels like

373
00:10:32,520 --> 00:10:34,000
leaving the real world.

374
00:10:34,000 --> 00:10:34,880
Yeah, exactly.

375
00:10:35,640 --> 00:10:36,640
Then I thought,

376
00:10:37,350 --> 00:10:38,280
could it be that

377
00:10:38,280 --> 00:10:40,030
the real world is like this?

378
00:10:40,440 --> 00:10:43,000
And when we're glued
to our phones too much,

379
00:10:43,000 --> 00:10:43,520
we can't

380
00:10:43,760 --> 00:10:44,200
(feel)

381
00:10:44,200 --> 00:10:44,590
anything.

382
00:10:45,880 --> 00:10:46,880
Previously, I really...

383
00:10:47,880 --> 00:10:48,840
super...

384
00:10:48,840 --> 00:10:49,760
couldn't leave my phone.

385
00:10:49,760 --> 00:10:50,590
But now it's not so bad.

386
00:10:51,030 --> 00:10:52,000
I think it's addicted.

387
00:10:52,000 --> 00:10:52,960
I mean,

388
00:10:52,960 --> 00:10:54,350
I have to check my phone
even in the shower.

389
00:10:54,590 --> 00:10:55,880
I wouldn't check it, but it would

390
00:10:55,880 --> 00:10:56,280
play music.

391
00:10:56,280 --> 00:10:57,960
I need it to make a sound.

392
00:10:57,960 --> 00:10:58,790
That's how I used to be.

393
00:10:58,790 --> 00:10:59,760
Then I turned

394
00:10:59,760 --> 00:11:01,030
to check my phone.

395
00:11:01,030 --> 00:11:01,550
So, how did you

396
00:11:01,550 --> 00:11:02,110
shower and look at (the phone)?

397
00:11:02,110 --> 00:11:02,960
Just shower like this.

398
00:11:02,960 --> 00:11:03,840
Did you even get clean?

399
00:11:04,350 --> 00:11:06,400
I'd scrub one side,
then put the phone down.

400
00:11:07,670 --> 00:11:09,440
Never got a shower clean.

401
00:11:09,440 --> 00:11:11,000
No wonder you're not as fair as I am.

402
00:11:11,060 --> 00:11:12,140
(Chocolate color, milk color)

403
00:11:14,280 --> 00:11:15,230
So, am I the messy one here?

404
00:11:15,230 --> 00:11:15,880
(Super casual comparison)
Yeah, haha.

405
00:11:17,320 --> 00:11:18,230
These past two days, I honestly feel

406
00:11:18,230 --> 00:11:19,230
like I've completely let loose.

407
00:11:19,320 --> 00:11:20,910
When I first got here, I was...

408
00:11:21,400 --> 00:11:22,080
a bit restrained.

409
00:11:22,280 --> 00:11:22,790
Kind of shy?

410
00:11:23,200 --> 00:11:23,910
Well, not exactly shy.

411
00:11:23,910 --> 00:11:25,520
You just need a little time

412
00:11:25,520 --> 00:11:26,520
to warm up to people.

413
00:11:26,520 --> 00:11:27,590
You can't just show up

414
00:11:27,590 --> 00:11:28,910
and babble a lot.

415
00:11:29,030 --> 00:11:29,960
When you first arrived,

416
00:11:29,960 --> 00:11:30,840
you probably didn't talk much either?

417
00:11:31,230 --> 00:11:32,760
I talked more with Jiawei.

418
00:11:32,840 --> 00:11:35,200
And I chatted with Guanjie in the room.

419
00:11:36,030 --> 00:11:37,200
Guanjie is adorable.

420
00:11:37,550 --> 00:11:38,440
Really adorable.

421
00:11:38,440 --> 00:11:39,590
Yeah, if Yan said something to him,

422
00:11:39,590 --> 00:11:41,440
he'd instantly turn
to tell the two of us.

423
00:11:44,000 --> 00:11:45,440
I think Yan is pretty funny.

424
00:11:45,590 --> 00:11:47,590
Yeah, at first she was quite serious.

425
00:11:47,590 --> 00:11:48,230
You know what I mean?

426
00:11:48,230 --> 00:11:50,000
But after interacting,
she's really adorable.

427
00:11:50,000 --> 00:11:50,670
Right.

428
00:11:51,150 --> 00:11:52,470
Like when I first met Yan...

429
00:11:52,470 --> 00:11:53,200
Guanjie had just arrived, too.

430
00:11:53,200 --> 00:11:54,080
And Yan kept not talking.

431
00:11:54,080 --> 00:11:54,960
Just sat there like this.

432
00:11:55,100 --> 00:11:56,340
(Exactly the same)

433
00:11:56,400 --> 00:11:57,110
She just kept doing that.

434
00:11:59,910 --> 00:12:01,030
I wanted to learn Cantonese before.

435
00:12:01,030 --> 00:12:02,440
But I just couldn't manage it.

436
00:12:02,550 --> 00:12:03,440
Have you tried learning it?

437
00:12:03,440 --> 00:12:04,230
Nope.

438
00:12:04,760 --> 00:12:05,320
Then...

439
00:12:05,320 --> 00:12:06,590
Hong Kong, China, and

440
00:12:06,590 --> 00:12:07,710
Guangzhou...

441
00:12:07,710 --> 00:12:08,960
Do people there
speak the same Cantonese?

442
00:12:08,960 --> 00:12:09,710
Is there a difference?

443
00:12:10,200 --> 00:12:11,030
You can hear it.

444
00:12:11,030 --> 00:12:12,280
Like some words...

445
00:12:12,280 --> 00:12:14,030
They exist in Hong Kong, China,

446
00:12:14,030 --> 00:12:14,910
but not in Guangzhou.

447
00:12:15,080 --> 00:12:17,030
Because the Cantonese in Guangzhou is

448
00:12:17,030 --> 00:12:18,320
what we usually

449
00:12:18,320 --> 00:12:19,350
learn in school.

450
00:12:20,110 --> 00:12:20,960
Formal written language.

451
00:12:21,320 --> 00:12:22,080
In Hong Kong, China,

452
00:12:22,080 --> 00:12:23,790
you'd have certain dialects.

453
00:12:23,790 --> 00:12:25,030
Right, right.

454
00:12:25,200 --> 00:12:25,550
Exactly.

455
00:12:26,030 --> 00:12:27,000
Including that saying you mentioned,

456
00:12:27,000 --> 00:12:27,710
I've never heard it before.

457
00:12:28,000 --> 00:12:28,710
What saying?

458
00:12:28,710 --> 00:12:29,280
That deer.

459
00:12:29,280 --> 00:12:30,080
Something about deer antlers.

460
00:12:31,150 --> 00:12:32,280
(This morning)
You're that kind of person,

461
00:12:32,280 --> 00:12:33,910
catching a deer
without removing its antlers.

462
00:12:33,910 --> 00:12:34,640
I didn't understand.

463
00:12:35,150 --> 00:12:37,320
It means when you catch a little deer...

464
00:12:37,320 --> 00:12:38,910
Its antlers are the most valuable part.

465
00:12:39,400 --> 00:12:40,200
But you just caught...

466
00:12:40,200 --> 00:12:41,230
I wouldn't do that.

467
00:12:41,670 --> 00:12:42,470
I'll do it for you then.

468
00:12:42,470 --> 00:12:43,550
I'm a kind person.

469
00:12:44,280 --> 00:12:45,110
Haven't you heard it before?

470
00:12:45,110 --> 00:12:45,840
Say it again.

471
00:12:46,230 --> 00:12:46,710
It means...

472
00:12:47,470 --> 00:12:48,790
Catching a deer
without removing its antlers.

473
00:12:48,790 --> 00:12:50,400
Catching a deer
without removing its antlers...

474
00:12:50,400 --> 00:12:51,200
In Mandarin?

475
00:12:51,200 --> 00:12:53,200
It means when you catch a little deer,

476
00:12:53,200 --> 00:12:55,110
its antlers are
the most valuable part, right?

477
00:12:55,520 --> 00:12:57,350
But you don't cherish the chance

478
00:12:57,350 --> 00:12:59,960
to pull them off.

479
00:12:59,960 --> 00:13:01,880
So basically,
it means you're kind of dumb.

480
00:13:02,020 --> 00:13:02,880
(Sharp)

481
00:13:02,880 --> 00:13:04,400
I thought you were saying
I'm kind-hearted.

482
00:13:04,910 --> 00:13:05,710
No.

483
00:13:05,710 --> 00:13:06,910
You meant I'm dumb, didn't you?

484
00:13:06,910 --> 00:13:07,520
Yeah.

485
00:13:07,580 --> 00:13:08,440
(Laughing in frustration)

486
00:13:08,440 --> 00:13:10,350
I really thought
too highly of you, Yang Tianyu.

487
00:13:10,470 --> 00:13:11,520
Well, I did mean kind, too.

488
00:13:11,620 --> 00:13:13,100
(Whatever you say)

489
00:13:20,440 --> 00:13:21,110
Do you have

490
00:13:21,110 --> 00:13:21,960
any siblings?

491
00:13:21,960 --> 00:13:22,670
I've got a younger brother.

492
00:13:22,790 --> 00:13:24,000
Did you ever pick on him?

493
00:13:24,000 --> 00:13:24,640
Yes.

494
00:13:27,280 --> 00:13:28,670
But now he's super nice to me.

495
00:13:28,760 --> 00:13:29,790
Because you pick on him.

496
00:13:29,790 --> 00:13:31,080
Because he wants
to stay on my good side.

497
00:13:31,080 --> 00:13:32,350
That's how he gets his pocket money.

498
00:13:32,350 --> 00:13:33,030
You know?

499
00:13:33,030 --> 00:13:34,350
When we were kids,
we fought all the time.

500
00:13:34,520 --> 00:13:35,440
Definitely.

501
00:13:36,000 --> 00:13:36,670
You fought, too?

502
00:13:36,670 --> 00:13:37,080
Yeah, I did.

503
00:13:37,080 --> 00:13:37,670
Every single day.

504
00:13:37,670 --> 00:13:38,840
What about your parents?

505
00:13:39,110 --> 00:13:39,960
They were always at work.

506
00:13:39,960 --> 00:13:40,470
Couldn't see?

507
00:13:40,470 --> 00:13:40,790
Yeah.

508
00:13:41,910 --> 00:13:43,200
Like the kind that ends with tears.

509
00:13:43,470 --> 00:13:44,760
Same here, my brother and I too.

510
00:13:44,760 --> 00:13:45,320
Right?

511
00:13:45,320 --> 00:13:46,880
But back then, when we were little,

512
00:13:47,110 --> 00:13:48,440
maybe at dinner,

513
00:13:48,440 --> 00:13:49,640
my parents might say
something wrong I did,

514
00:13:49,640 --> 00:13:51,440
then my brother would act
sarcastically and mean.

515
00:13:51,760 --> 00:13:52,470
And I'd get super mad.

516
00:13:52,470 --> 00:13:53,640
So I'd throw my chopsticks at him.

517
00:13:53,960 --> 00:13:55,440
He wouldn't take it
and started fighting back.

518
00:13:55,440 --> 00:13:56,910
My parents just thought no matter

519
00:13:56,910 --> 00:13:57,960
who they sided with, it'd be unfair.

520
00:13:58,280 --> 00:13:59,590
They didn't want to play favorites.

521
00:13:59,590 --> 00:14:00,470
So they'd watch us fight.

522
00:14:01,710 --> 00:14:02,520
That's how it is?

523
00:14:02,520 --> 00:14:03,000
Yeah.

524
00:14:03,350 --> 00:14:05,280
But I think as we get older,

525
00:14:05,280 --> 00:14:06,520
we'll end up caring about each other.

526
00:14:06,840 --> 00:14:08,030
Yeah, for sure.

527
00:14:08,150 --> 00:14:09,400
If you never fought as kids,

528
00:14:09,400 --> 00:14:11,150
you probably wouldn't
stay friends as adults.

529
00:14:11,470 --> 00:14:12,150
I think so.

530
00:14:12,910 --> 00:14:13,790
A little fighting is necessary.

531
00:14:14,580 --> 00:14:16,860
(The more you fight,
the closer you feel)

532
00:14:17,550 --> 00:14:19,030
What's your favorite animal?

533
00:14:19,030 --> 00:14:20,440
I love puppies the most.

534
00:14:20,960 --> 00:14:22,150
Not a fan of cats?

535
00:14:22,280 --> 00:14:23,230
I like dogs more.

536
00:14:23,520 --> 00:14:24,200
Same here.

537
00:14:24,200 --> 00:14:24,840
Really?

538
00:14:25,840 --> 00:14:27,280
I thought you'd be more into cats.

539
00:14:27,280 --> 00:14:28,080
Not really.

540
00:14:28,230 --> 00:14:30,000
I like those sweet,
playful little puppies.

541
00:14:30,000 --> 00:14:32,440
The kind that wags its tail at me
every time I come home.

542
00:14:32,440 --> 00:14:34,760
Because a lot of my friends
are into cats.

543
00:14:34,760 --> 00:14:35,350
Yeah.

544
00:14:35,350 --> 00:14:36,880
I thought you liked cats, too.

545
00:14:37,080 --> 00:14:38,200
For a few years,

546
00:14:38,320 --> 00:14:39,150
all of a sudden,

547
00:14:39,150 --> 00:14:41,200
so many of my friends became cat lovers.

548
00:14:41,790 --> 00:14:43,470
I found it kind of strange.

549
00:14:43,470 --> 00:14:45,520
I thought your personality seemed
more like a cat person.

550
00:14:45,520 --> 00:14:46,080
No.

551
00:14:46,440 --> 00:14:47,840
You don't even know what I'm like.

552
00:14:50,520 --> 00:14:52,350
Will they edit in my eye-rolls?

553
00:14:52,350 --> 00:14:53,640
Roll my eyes at you every day.

554
00:14:54,030 --> 00:14:55,150
Enlarge them.

555
00:14:55,280 --> 00:14:56,280
That would be ugly.

556
00:14:56,700 --> 00:14:59,540
(Kind of cute)

557
00:15:00,550 --> 00:15:02,520
Do you usually do romantic things?

558
00:15:03,400 --> 00:15:04,710
You're a super unromantic person.

559
00:15:04,710 --> 00:15:05,400
No.

560
00:15:05,400 --> 00:15:06,030
Don't do it?

561
00:15:06,030 --> 00:15:06,710
Don't.

562
00:15:07,030 --> 00:15:08,080
Do you like romantic things?

563
00:15:08,080 --> 00:15:10,200
I like things
with a little sense of occasion.

564
00:15:10,200 --> 00:15:11,790
Like what?

565
00:15:11,790 --> 00:15:13,840
For example, holidays,

566
00:15:13,840 --> 00:15:15,670
birthdays, or things like that.

567
00:15:15,670 --> 00:15:16,960
I just hope everyone
treats those moments

568
00:15:16,960 --> 00:15:17,760
like they actually matter.

569
00:15:18,200 --> 00:15:19,150
That would happen.

570
00:15:19,150 --> 00:15:20,590
Does this count as romantic?

571
00:15:20,590 --> 00:15:21,640
Isn't this basic?

572
00:15:21,640 --> 00:15:22,760
But I also don't want things to feel

573
00:15:22,760 --> 00:15:24,640
too over...

574
00:15:25,200 --> 00:15:27,230
Just go to a nice restaurant,

575
00:15:27,230 --> 00:15:29,000
get a cake or something.

576
00:15:29,000 --> 00:15:29,470
Yeah.

577
00:15:29,470 --> 00:15:30,280
Maybe bring some flowers too.

578
00:15:30,670 --> 00:15:31,790
That counts as romantic?

579
00:15:32,280 --> 00:15:33,470
It's all about that sense of ritual.

580
00:15:34,200 --> 00:15:35,320
But a lot of people

581
00:15:35,320 --> 00:15:36,440
don't even realize it.

582
00:15:36,440 --> 00:15:37,230
They don't

583
00:15:37,230 --> 00:15:38,030
think

584
00:15:38,030 --> 00:15:39,550
holidays matter.

585
00:15:39,710 --> 00:15:41,200
Then I actually like
a sense of occasion.

586
00:15:41,200 --> 00:15:41,760
Yeah.

587
00:15:41,760 --> 00:15:43,400
But I wouldn't call myself romantic.

588
00:15:43,400 --> 00:15:44,280
Even if I do these things,

589
00:15:44,280 --> 00:15:46,080
I don't see them as romantic acts.

590
00:15:46,080 --> 00:15:46,760
Okay.

591
00:15:47,060 --> 00:15:48,420
(Favorability +1)

592
00:15:53,470 --> 00:15:54,400
We're here.

593
00:15:56,520 --> 00:15:57,880
Eat seafood or something.

594
00:15:57,880 --> 00:15:59,110
Sure, sounds good.

595
00:16:02,030 --> 00:16:03,150
I wanted to pull your chair for you.

596
00:16:03,150 --> 00:16:03,670
Okay, go ahead.

597
00:16:03,670 --> 00:16:04,790
Nah, forget it.

598
00:16:04,790 --> 00:16:05,960
Do it.

599
00:16:16,910 --> 00:16:18,590
I'm now in a state

600
00:16:18,590 --> 00:16:20,710
of quietly waiting for food.

601
00:16:21,000 --> 00:16:21,790
Here comes the food.

602
00:16:23,520 --> 00:16:24,960
Instantly cheered up.

603
00:16:24,960 --> 00:16:26,000
Alright, thanks.

604
00:16:26,710 --> 00:16:27,710
Thanks.

605
00:16:33,200 --> 00:16:33,880
Is it good?

606
00:16:34,520 --> 00:16:35,080
Really good.

607
00:16:35,790 --> 00:16:36,960
Feels like we're at the seaside.

608
00:16:38,060 --> 00:16:40,580
(The sea and food match better)

609
00:16:41,910 --> 00:16:42,880
For some reason,

610
00:16:42,880 --> 00:16:46,080
when we're in this restaurant,

611
00:16:46,080 --> 00:16:46,550
we start

612
00:16:46,550 --> 00:16:47,030
talking quietly.

613
00:16:47,030 --> 00:16:48,670
But I'm sure the mic can still catch it.

614
00:16:49,200 --> 00:16:50,230
Don't worry about it.

615
00:16:50,230 --> 00:16:51,880
(Relax, I've got this)

616
00:16:51,880 --> 00:16:53,960
Everyone just gets more polite
in places like this.

617
00:16:54,060 --> 00:16:55,660
(Talking nonsense again)

618
00:16:59,230 --> 00:17:00,550
If we run out of things to say,

619
00:17:00,550 --> 00:17:01,840
would that feel awkward to you?

620
00:17:01,840 --> 00:17:02,550
Not at all.

621
00:17:02,550 --> 00:17:03,320
Same here.

622
00:17:03,880 --> 00:17:04,880
I think it's pretty nice.

623
00:17:04,880 --> 00:17:05,470
Right?

624
00:17:05,470 --> 00:17:06,230
Yeah.

625
00:17:06,230 --> 00:17:08,560
When two people are together,

626
00:17:08,560 --> 00:17:09,760
(The focus is on comfort)
each doing their own thing,

627
00:17:09,760 --> 00:17:10,920
just hanging out in the same space...

628
00:17:10,920 --> 00:17:11,520
That's good enough.

629
00:17:11,950 --> 00:17:13,710
We can't talk nonsense
all the time, right?

630
00:17:13,710 --> 00:17:14,710
That's empty chatter.

631
00:17:14,920 --> 00:17:16,160
If there's nothing to say,
just be quiet.

632
00:17:16,160 --> 00:17:16,710
Right.

633
00:17:18,830 --> 00:17:21,190
Feels like it's our first date today.

634
00:17:21,350 --> 00:17:24,070
But the day before yesterday
felt like the second.

635
00:17:24,070 --> 00:17:25,310
Why did that feel like the second one,

636
00:17:25,310 --> 00:17:26,350
and today the first?

637
00:17:26,680 --> 00:17:27,000
No idea.

638
00:17:27,000 --> 00:17:28,160
Maybe it's the vibe here.

639
00:17:28,160 --> 00:17:29,710
It just feels more like the first time?

640
00:17:29,710 --> 00:17:29,950
Yeah.

641
00:17:29,950 --> 00:17:30,760
Yes.

642
00:17:30,760 --> 00:17:31,760
The second felt like

643
00:17:31,760 --> 00:17:33,000
we were already familiar.

644
00:17:41,430 --> 00:17:43,400
Would you

645
00:17:43,400 --> 00:17:44,470
prefer dates

646
00:17:44,880 --> 00:17:47,520
to be like this environment,

647
00:17:47,680 --> 00:17:48,950
or something more casual?

648
00:17:48,950 --> 00:17:51,230
I care more about

649
00:17:51,230 --> 00:17:53,190
the activity beyond just eating.

650
00:17:53,190 --> 00:17:54,590
Yeah, I think having fun matters more.

651
00:17:55,040 --> 00:17:55,800
As for eating...

652
00:17:55,800 --> 00:17:57,710
Even if it's not some fancy meal,

653
00:17:57,710 --> 00:17:59,310
just eating at a street stall,

654
00:17:59,310 --> 00:18:00,800
everyone still
eats happily and leaves full.

655
00:18:02,760 --> 00:18:04,350
Are you happy on the island?

656
00:18:04,680 --> 00:18:05,470
Yeah.

657
00:18:05,470 --> 00:18:06,710
You've been happy since you arrived?

658
00:18:07,110 --> 00:18:08,070
It's just that...

659
00:18:08,070 --> 00:18:09,950
I imagined it wouldn't be this good.

660
00:18:09,950 --> 00:18:11,560
So when I came in,

661
00:18:11,560 --> 00:18:12,710
I thought it was pretty good.

662
00:18:12,710 --> 00:18:14,430
But actually, I do feel...

663
00:18:15,710 --> 00:18:17,920
occasionally a bit unhappy.

664
00:18:17,920 --> 00:18:18,920
Why's that?

665
00:18:18,920 --> 00:18:19,800
Because...

666
00:18:19,800 --> 00:18:21,640
I'm not too fond

667
00:18:21,640 --> 00:18:22,430
of parting.

668
00:18:25,160 --> 00:18:27,830
It's a mix of complicated emotions.

669
00:18:27,830 --> 00:18:29,430
I just can't stand that kind of thing.

670
00:18:29,430 --> 00:18:31,400
But I also think

671
00:18:31,400 --> 00:18:32,520
this is really

672
00:18:32,520 --> 00:18:32,880
precious.

673
00:18:32,880 --> 00:18:34,400
This feeling.

674
00:18:34,590 --> 00:18:36,430
Like yesterday, wasn't I supposed

675
00:18:36,430 --> 00:18:37,920
to think of three questions?

676
00:18:38,280 --> 00:18:40,190
I was in my room, thinking about them,

677
00:18:40,190 --> 00:18:41,760
and then I thought,

678
00:18:41,760 --> 00:18:43,880
"Forget it, I don't want
to think about anything."

679
00:18:43,880 --> 00:18:45,310
It felt like too much pressure.

680
00:18:46,280 --> 00:18:47,800
Is there something you want to ask?

681
00:18:47,800 --> 00:18:49,230
Does this thing scare you?

682
00:18:49,230 --> 00:18:50,680
Actually, a little bit.

683
00:18:52,160 --> 00:18:53,560
Yeah, I know.

684
00:18:53,560 --> 00:18:54,520
If I asked those questions,

685
00:18:54,520 --> 00:18:55,470
you'd definitely feel pressured.

686
00:18:55,470 --> 00:18:56,560
So I figured I'd ask something

687
00:18:56,560 --> 00:18:57,590
a bit more lighthearted and fun.

688
00:18:57,880 --> 00:18:58,470
Yeah.

689
00:18:58,470 --> 00:18:59,430
I do get you, right?

690
00:19:08,710 --> 00:19:09,560
Have you ever tried

691
00:19:09,800 --> 00:19:10,800
being in a long-distance relationship?

692
00:19:11,520 --> 00:19:12,110
In a relationship?

693
00:19:12,110 --> 00:19:12,560
Yeah.

694
00:19:14,000 --> 00:19:15,640
My ex and I were long-distance.

695
00:19:16,520 --> 00:19:17,230
It ended

696
00:19:17,230 --> 00:19:18,560
because of

697
00:19:19,110 --> 00:19:19,950
the distance...?

698
00:19:19,950 --> 00:19:20,680
Or something else?

699
00:19:21,590 --> 00:19:23,110
It wasn't just the distance.

700
00:19:23,110 --> 00:19:23,710
It's...

701
00:19:23,710 --> 00:19:25,520
We dated for a year and a half.

702
00:19:25,520 --> 00:19:27,400
Then, later on, maybe,

703
00:19:27,400 --> 00:19:28,640
we both started
to feel that communication

704
00:19:28,800 --> 00:19:30,400
was getting a bit hard.

705
00:19:30,950 --> 00:19:31,680
I see.

706
00:19:32,760 --> 00:19:33,520
So what was

707
00:19:33,520 --> 00:19:35,110
your most heartbreaking breakup about?

708
00:19:37,110 --> 00:19:40,110
When we broke up,

709
00:19:40,110 --> 00:19:41,190
we were still in love.

710
00:19:41,560 --> 00:19:42,590
Then why did you break up?

711
00:19:43,040 --> 00:19:45,710
Maybe it was
a matter of different values.

712
00:19:45,710 --> 00:19:46,760
That sounds pretty rational of you two.

713
00:19:47,430 --> 00:19:48,710
If I were still in love,

714
00:19:48,710 --> 00:19:50,470
I probably wouldn't choose to separate,

715
00:19:50,470 --> 00:19:51,710
even if we weren't really a good match.

716
00:19:52,160 --> 00:19:53,230
I think I'm the kind of person

717
00:19:53,230 --> 00:19:55,160
who won't force myself

718
00:19:55,160 --> 00:19:57,110
to accept her flaws.

719
00:19:57,110 --> 00:20:00,000
Like, I know what her flaws are,

720
00:20:00,430 --> 00:20:02,190
but I'd still love her.

721
00:20:02,190 --> 00:20:03,230
Then...

722
00:20:03,230 --> 00:20:04,760
you wouldn't have to break up.

723
00:20:05,560 --> 00:20:07,430
No, but once it reaches a point,

724
00:20:07,430 --> 00:20:09,190
it just...

725
00:20:09,190 --> 00:20:10,520
It couldn't continue.

726
00:20:10,520 --> 00:20:11,110
Yeah.

727
00:20:15,040 --> 00:20:15,880
So you're the type

728
00:20:15,880 --> 00:20:16,760
who likes when you like,

729
00:20:16,760 --> 00:20:17,400
and stops when you don't?

730
00:20:17,400 --> 00:20:18,590
Yeah, I'm the kind of person

731
00:20:18,800 --> 00:20:20,160
who doesn't have much patience.

732
00:20:21,110 --> 00:20:21,590
If I don't like it,

733
00:20:21,590 --> 00:20:22,800
it doesn't matter
how nice you are to me.

734
00:20:23,070 --> 00:20:24,430
But if I do like you, even if you're not

735
00:20:24,430 --> 00:20:25,280
that nice to me,

736
00:20:25,520 --> 00:20:27,160
I'll still think
you're pretty good to me.

737
00:20:33,040 --> 00:20:34,040
Let's go.

738
00:20:37,640 --> 00:20:38,310
The beach.

739
00:20:39,040 --> 00:20:40,590
I haven't been to the beach before.

740
00:20:40,590 --> 00:20:42,110
I want to take my shoes off
and go in the water.

741
00:20:42,590 --> 00:20:43,430
Then let's go now.

742
00:20:44,350 --> 00:20:45,560
This is so comfortable.

743
00:20:46,470 --> 00:20:47,800
Even the mood is lifted.

744
00:20:47,800 --> 00:20:48,350
Yeah.

745
00:20:58,310 --> 00:20:59,680
Don't go too low.

746
00:21:00,110 --> 00:21:01,280
I want to wash my hands.

747
00:21:01,280 --> 00:21:01,800
Go ahead.

748
00:21:14,430 --> 00:21:16,350
I'm done playing with you, Yang Tianyu.

749
00:21:18,950 --> 00:21:20,070
Truce!

750
00:21:21,760 --> 00:21:22,880
Careful.

751
00:21:22,880 --> 00:21:23,640
Okay.

752
00:21:24,040 --> 00:21:25,000
Feels so nice.

753
00:21:28,350 --> 00:21:29,920
This is honestly so romantic.

754
00:21:32,680 --> 00:21:33,950
I love being by the sea.

755
00:21:34,760 --> 00:21:36,070
The sea!

756
00:21:46,590 --> 00:21:47,560
I think...

757
00:21:47,560 --> 00:21:49,070
your left and right sides look the same.

758
00:21:49,430 --> 00:21:50,830
No, you just don't get it.

759
00:21:50,830 --> 00:21:51,350
Dull man.

760
00:21:51,350 --> 00:21:52,280
I'll show you later.

761
00:21:52,280 --> 00:21:53,470
I think the sides of my face
look different.

762
00:21:53,900 --> 00:21:55,140
(Observing closely)

763
00:21:56,110 --> 00:21:57,110
No difference.

764
00:21:57,110 --> 00:21:57,950
Yes, there is!

765
00:21:58,920 --> 00:21:59,560
You don't understand.

766
00:22:02,470 --> 00:22:03,680
Is my hair really messy?

767
00:22:04,760 --> 00:22:05,190
Is it alright?

768
00:22:06,070 --> 00:22:06,560
It's messy.

769
00:22:06,560 --> 00:22:07,710
Messy, but it suits you.

770
00:22:09,470 --> 00:22:10,830
Now you're not making cheeky comments.

771
00:22:11,350 --> 00:22:13,710
The lie detector shows...

772
00:22:13,710 --> 00:22:14,520
That's a lie.

773
00:22:14,520 --> 00:22:15,680
A lie.

774
00:22:22,710 --> 00:22:23,590
Are we going or not?

775
00:22:23,590 --> 00:22:24,190
Let's go.

776
00:22:29,680 --> 00:22:30,190
I'll sit on this side.

777
00:22:30,880 --> 00:22:31,350
You sit on that side.

778
00:22:36,110 --> 00:22:36,520
Looks beautiful.

779
00:22:36,520 --> 00:22:37,560
The setting's pretty nice.

780
00:22:37,560 --> 00:22:38,640
It's stunning.

781
00:22:40,590 --> 00:22:42,280
I've never been on such a formal date.

782
00:22:42,280 --> 00:22:43,760
Me neither.

783
00:22:44,620 --> 00:22:46,140
(Awkward)

784
00:22:46,160 --> 00:22:48,000
So you don't usually come
to places like this?

785
00:22:48,640 --> 00:22:49,800
You know, this kind of vibe.

786
00:22:52,430 --> 00:22:53,470
Sometimes.

787
00:22:53,880 --> 00:22:54,760
Under what circumstances?

788
00:22:55,430 --> 00:22:56,310
A gathering...

789
00:22:56,310 --> 00:22:58,070
Eating with family...

790
00:22:58,070 --> 00:22:58,800
I've had that too.

791
00:22:59,680 --> 00:23:00,310
Same here.

792
00:23:02,880 --> 00:23:04,160
Do you think
they're thinking about things

793
00:23:04,160 --> 00:23:05,160
when they swim?

794
00:23:05,160 --> 00:23:06,640
(Me?)

795
00:23:06,640 --> 00:23:07,920
Or maybe fish don't think at all,

796
00:23:07,920 --> 00:23:08,880
they just swim?

797
00:23:08,880 --> 00:23:09,640
Just keep swimming.

798
00:23:09,640 --> 00:23:10,710
No thoughts.

799
00:23:11,310 --> 00:23:12,350
Sometimes I feel like I'm the same way.

800
00:23:12,350 --> 00:23:13,400
Like I'm turning

801
00:23:13,400 --> 00:23:13,640
into

802
00:23:13,640 --> 00:23:14,470
a fish.

803
00:23:14,470 --> 00:23:15,560
Seven-second memory.

804
00:23:16,040 --> 00:23:17,880
Say something and forget it right after.

805
00:23:19,400 --> 00:23:20,160
Like what?

806
00:23:21,590 --> 00:23:22,400
Happens with so many things.

807
00:23:22,400 --> 00:23:23,760
Feels like I'm getting older.

808
00:23:23,760 --> 00:23:25,000
(Young but feels ancient)
Brain fog is creeping in.

809
00:23:25,000 --> 00:23:25,520
That's me, right?

810
00:23:25,520 --> 00:23:26,110
Every single day,

811
00:23:26,560 --> 00:23:28,640
I ask what happened, and I forget.

812
00:23:28,640 --> 00:23:29,350
Same here.

813
00:23:32,000 --> 00:23:32,800
Thanks.

814
00:23:35,040 --> 00:23:36,430
So, would this kind of environment be

815
00:23:36,950 --> 00:23:37,710
somewhere you'd

816
00:23:37,710 --> 00:23:38,880
take a girl on a date?

817
00:23:39,470 --> 00:23:40,190
No.

818
00:23:40,190 --> 00:23:40,920
No?

819
00:23:41,190 --> 00:23:42,190
You think it's too

820
00:23:43,000 --> 00:23:43,830
out of the ordinary?

821
00:23:44,190 --> 00:23:44,950
Yeah.

822
00:23:44,950 --> 00:23:46,000
But I think

823
00:23:46,000 --> 00:23:47,110
this kind of scene

824
00:23:47,110 --> 00:23:48,590
is definitely necessary.

825
00:23:49,350 --> 00:23:51,590
When would you need this kind of scene?

826
00:23:51,590 --> 00:23:53,920
Seriously, it feels like
a proposal scene.

827
00:23:55,230 --> 00:23:56,470
It's way too formal.

828
00:23:56,470 --> 00:23:57,950
Because if this is supposed
to be everyday life,

829
00:23:57,950 --> 00:23:59,520
what do you do for a proposal?

830
00:23:59,520 --> 00:24:00,310
You might have to

831
00:24:00,310 --> 00:24:01,430
rent out

832
00:24:01,430 --> 00:24:02,640
Disneyland.

833
00:24:04,160 --> 00:24:05,590
You really haven't been to Disneyland?

834
00:24:06,230 --> 00:24:06,710
Really haven't.

835
00:24:06,710 --> 00:24:07,590
How is that possible?

836
00:24:08,280 --> 00:24:09,110
Seriously.

837
00:24:09,110 --> 00:24:10,230
When I was a kid,

838
00:24:10,950 --> 00:24:12,000
I always...

839
00:24:12,000 --> 00:24:13,430
grew up in Shandong.

840
00:24:13,640 --> 00:24:14,640
So what did you do there?

841
00:24:15,400 --> 00:24:16,000
Study for the civil service exam?

842
00:24:16,880 --> 00:24:17,830
Yeah, studying.

843
00:24:17,830 --> 00:24:18,640
Studying in Shandong.

844
00:24:18,640 --> 00:24:18,950
Really?

845
00:24:19,760 --> 00:24:20,830
Yeah, and I barely had any free time.

846
00:24:20,830 --> 00:24:21,920
Never really went out to have fun.

847
00:24:21,920 --> 00:24:23,560
So, did you study well?

848
00:24:23,560 --> 00:24:24,070
Fairly average.

849
00:24:25,280 --> 00:24:26,560
I felt like...

850
00:24:26,560 --> 00:24:27,110
When I was a kid,

851
00:24:27,880 --> 00:24:28,800
my parents were

852
00:24:29,230 --> 00:24:30,470
pretty strict.

853
00:24:31,590 --> 00:24:32,640
Strict in what way?

854
00:24:32,640 --> 00:24:33,230
Like, regarding

855
00:24:33,760 --> 00:24:34,430
your life?

856
00:24:35,000 --> 00:24:35,350
Grades?

857
00:24:35,350 --> 00:24:35,950
Pretty much everything.

858
00:24:35,950 --> 00:24:36,310
Grades?

859
00:24:36,310 --> 00:24:37,110
Yeah, grades.

860
